Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the codes in different regions, which involves analyzing the behavior of the system, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves constructing a family of codes, which could be considered as a data structure problem, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves simulations and experiments, which could be related to network infrastructure, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a possible sub-category.
